IP
The internet protocol is how devices communicate with eachother over the network.
Each device is assigned either a static or dynamic IP address.

Transmission Control Protocol - TCP
Connection oriented. Sender and reciever must first establish connection with a 3 way handshake.
SYN
ACK


Fast recovery
TCP Tahoe
TCP Reno


User Datagram Protocol - UDP
Connectionless, no handshake needed to establish connection.


OSI model
-------------
Physical layer 
Raw bit stream (1s 0s) over physical medium such as cables.

Data link Layer - MAC

Network layer - IP

Transmission Layer - TCP

Session layer 
Connection management 

Presentation Layer - 

Application Layer - 
